# 📊 Job Application Tracker (Full Stack Project)

A simple full-stack web application to track job applications through different hiring stages such as Applied, Interviewing, Offer, and Rejected.

This project is built as part of the **InternSathi Full Stack Internship Assignment**.

---

## 🚀 Project Overview

The Job Application Tracker helps users manage and monitor their job applications in one place.

### ✨ Features
- Add job applications
- View all applications in dashboard
- Edit/update application details
- Delete applications
- Filter by status (Applied, Interviewing, Offer, Rejected)
- Search by company or job title
- Responsive UI (mobile + desktop)
- Pagination (frontend)

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack Used

### Frontend
- React + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Axios
- React Router DOM

### Backend
- Node.js
- Express.js
- Prisma ORM

### Database
- MySQL

---

## 📦 Prerequisites

Make sure you have installed:

- Node.js
- npm
- MySQL Server
- Git

---

## ⚙️ Installation Steps

### 1. Clone repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/hark07/mini_job_tracker.git
cd mini_job_tracker

### 2. Backend setup
- cd backend
- npm install

### 3. Setup environment variables

- Create .env file inside backend:

  DATABASE_URL="mysql://root:password@localhost:3306/job_tracker"
  PORT=5000
### 4. Prisma setup
- npx prisma generate
- npx prisma migrate dev --name init
## 5. Run backend (development mode)
- npm run dev

## Backend runs at:

 http://localhost:5000
### 6. Frontend setup
- cd frontend
- npm install
- npm run dev

## Frontend runs at:
 http://localhost:5173

